40template <class T>
41inline T sgn(const T x) {
42 T zero(0);
43 T one(1);
44 return (x == zero ? zero : (x < zero ? -one : one));
45}

49template <typename T>
50struct ApplyGradientDescent<CPUDevice, T> {
51 void operator()(const CPUDevice& d, typename TTypes<T>::Flat var,
52 typename TTypes<T>::ConstScalar lr,
53 typename TTypes<T>::ConstFlat grad) {
54 var.device(d) -= grad * lr();
55 }
56};
57
58#ifdef TENSORFLOW_USE_SYCL
59template <typename T>
60struct ApplyGradientDescentSYCL {
61 void operator()(const SYCLDevice& d, typename TTypes<T>::Flat var, T lr,
62 typename TTypes<T>::ConstFlat grad) {
63 var.device(d) -= grad * lr;
64 }
65};
66#endif

68template <typename T>
69struct ApplyAdadelta<CPUDevice, T> {
70 void operator()(const CPUDevice& d, typename TTypes<T>::Flat var,
71 typename TTypes<T>::Flat accum,
72 typename TTypes<T>::Flat accum_update,
73 typename TTypes<T>::ConstScalar lr,
74 typename TTypes<T>::ConstScalar rho,
75 typename TTypes<T>::ConstScalar epsilon,
76 typename TTypes<T>::ConstFlat grad) {
77 accum.device(d) =
78 accum * rho() + grad.square() * (static_cast<T>(1) - rho());
79 const auto update =
80 (accum_update + epsilon()).sqrt() * (accum + epsilon()).rsqrt() * grad;
81 var.device(d) -= update * lr();
82 accum_update.device(d) =
83 accum_update * rho() + update.square() * (static_cast<T>(1) - rho());
84 }
85};
86
87template <typename T>
88struct ApplyProximalGradientDescent<CPUDevice, T> {
89 void operator()(const CPUDevice& d, typename TTypes<T>::Flat var,
90 typename TTypes<T>::ConstScalar lr,
91 typename TTypes<T>::ConstScalar l1,
92 typename TTypes<T>::ConstScalar l2,
93 typename TTypes<T>::ConstFlat grad) {
94 // Note that here is Fobos update, for details please refer:
95 // http://papers.nips.cc/paper/3793-efficient-learning-using-forward-backward-splitting.pdf
96 // TODO(xbing): merge the logic for ProximalGradientDescent and
97 // ProximalAdagrad.
98 auto prox_var = var;
99 // compute v = w - lr * grad.
100 prox_var.device(d) -= grad * lr();
101 if (l1() > 0) {
102 // compute sign(v) * max(|v| - lr * l1, 0)
103 var.device(d) =
104 prox_var.sign() *
105 (prox_var.abs() - var.constant(lr() * l1())).cwiseMax(T(0.0)) /
106 (var.constant(1.0) + var.constant(l2() * lr()));
107 } else {
108 var.device(d) =
109 prox_var / (var.constant(1.0) + var.constant(l2() * lr()));
110 }
111 }
112};
113
114template <typename T>
115struct ApplyAdagradDA<CPUDevice, T> {
116 void operator()(const CPUDevice& d, typename TTypes<T>::Flat var,
117 typename TTypes<T>::Flat gradient_accum,
118 typename TTypes<T>::Flat gradient_squared_accum,
119 typename TTypes<T>::ConstScalar lr, int64 global_step,
120 typename TTypes<T>::ConstScalar l1,
121 typename TTypes<T>::ConstScalar l2,
122 typename TTypes<T>::ConstFlat grad) {
123 // Accumulate gradient, and gradient_squared
124 gradient_accum.device(d) += grad;
125 gradient_squared_accum.device(d) += grad.square();
126
127 // AdagradDA update:
128 // Let g to be gradient accumulator, gg to be gradient squared accumulator,
129 // T be the global step, lr is the learning rate, and k the initial
130 // gradient squared accumulator value.
131 // w = \dfrac{sign(-g)*lr*|g - l1*T|_{+}}{l2*T*lr + \sqrt{k+gg})}
132 if (l1() > 0) {
133 var.device(d) =
134 lr() * var.constant(-1.0) * gradient_accum.sign() *
135 (gradient_accum.abs() -
136 var.constant(static_cast<float>(global_step)) * var.constant(l1()))
137 .cwiseMax(T(0.0)) /
138 (var.constant(l2()) *
139 var.constant(static_cast<float>(global_step) * lr()) +
140 gradient_squared_accum.sqrt());
141 } else {
142 var.device(d) =
143 lr() * gradient_accum * var.constant(-1.0) /
144 (var.constant(l2()) *
145 var.constant(static_cast<float>(global_step) * lr()) +
146 gradient_squared_accum.sqrt());
147 }
148 }
149};
150
151template <typename T>
152struct ApplyAdagrad<CPUDevice, T> {
153 void operator()(const CPUDevice& d, typename TTypes<T>::Flat var,
154 typename TTypes<T>::Flat accum,
155 typename TTypes<T>::ConstScalar lr,
156 typename TTypes<T>::ConstFlat grad) {
157 accum.device(d) += grad.square();
158 var.device(d) -= grad * lr() * accum.rsqrt();
159 }
160};
161
162template <typename T>
163struct ApplyProximalAdagrad<CPUDevice, T> {
164 void operator()(const CPUDevice& d, typename TTypes<T>::Flat var,
165 typename TTypes<T>::Flat accum,
166 typename TTypes<T>::ConstScalar lr,
167 typename TTypes<T>::ConstScalar l1,
168 typename TTypes<T>::ConstScalar l2,
169 typename TTypes<T>::ConstFlat grad) {
170 // Fobos update per paper with Adagrad learning rate.
171 accum.device(d) += grad.square();
172 // Adagrad learning rate.
173 auto learning_rate = accum.constant(lr()) * accum.rsqrt();
174 auto prox_var = var;
175 // compute v = w - lr * grad.
176 prox_var.device(d) -= grad * learning_rate;
177 if (l1() > 0) {
178 // compute sign(v) * max(|v| - lr * l1, 0)
179 var.device(d) = prox_var.sign() *
180 (prox_var.abs() - learning_rate * prox_var.constant(l1()))
181 .cwiseMax(T(0.0)) /
182 (var.constant(1.0) + var.constant(l2()) * learning_rate);
183 } else {
184 var.device(d) =
185 prox_var / (var.constant(1.0) + var.constant(l2()) * learning_rate);
186 }
187 }
188};

190template <typename T>
191struct ApplyFtrlV2<CPUDevice, T> {
192 void operator()(const CPUDevice& d, typename TTypes<T>::Flat var,
193 typename TTypes<T>::Flat accum,
194 typename TTypes<T>::Flat linear,
195 typename TTypes<T>::ConstFlat grad,
196 typename TTypes<T>::ConstScalar lr,
197 typename TTypes<T>::ConstScalar l1,
198 typename TTypes<T>::ConstScalar l2,
199 typename TTypes<T>::ConstScalar l2_shrinkage,
200 typename TTypes<T>::ConstScalar lr_power) {
201 auto grad_with_shrinkage = grad + static_cast<T>(2) * l2_shrinkage() * var;
202 auto new_accum = accum + grad_with_shrinkage.square();
203 // special case for which lr_power=-0.5.
204 if (lr_power() == static_cast<T>(-0.5)) {
205 linear.device(d) +=
206 grad_with_shrinkage - (new_accum.sqrt() - accum.sqrt()) / lr() * var;
207 } else {
208 linear.device(d) +=
209 grad_with_shrinkage -
210 (new_accum.pow(-lr_power()) - accum.pow(-lr_power())) / lr() * var;
211 }
212 auto x = (linear.constant(l1()) * linear.sign() - linear);
213 if (lr_power() == static_cast<T>(-0.5)) {
214 auto y = new_accum.sqrt() / new_accum.constant(lr()) +
215 linear.constant(static_cast<T>(2) * l2());
216 auto pre_shrink = x / y;
217 var.device(d) = (linear.abs() > linear.constant(l1()))
218 .select(pre_shrink, var.constant(static_cast<T>(0)));
219
220 } else {
221 auto y = new_accum.pow(-lr_power()) / new_accum.constant(lr()) +
222 linear.constant(static_cast<T>(2) * l2());
223 auto pre_shrink = x / y;
224 var.device(d) = (linear.abs() > linear.constant(l1()))
225 .select(pre_shrink, var.constant(static_cast<T>(0)));
226 }
227 accum.device(d) += grad_with_shrinkage.square();
228 }
229};
230
231template <typename T>
232struct ApplyFtrl<CPUDevice, T> {
233 void operator()(const CPUDevice& d, typename TTypes<T>::Flat var,
234 typename TTypes<T>::Flat accum,
235 typename TTypes<T>::Flat linear,
236 typename TTypes<T>::ConstFlat grad,
237 typename TTypes<T>::ConstScalar lr,
238 typename TTypes<T>::ConstScalar l1,
239 typename TTypes<T>::ConstScalar l2,
240 typename TTypes<T>::ConstScalar lr_power) {
241 auto new_accum = accum + grad.square();
242 // special case for which lr_power=-0.5.
243 if (lr_power() == static_cast<T>(-0.5)) {
244 linear.device(d) += grad - (new_accum.sqrt() - accum.sqrt()) / lr() * var;
245 } else {
246 linear.device(d) +=
247 grad -
248 (new_accum.pow(-lr_power()) - accum.pow(-lr_power())) / lr() * var;
249 }
250 auto x = (linear.constant(l1()) * linear.sign() - linear);
251 if (lr_power() == static_cast<T>(-0.5)) {
252 auto y = new_accum.sqrt() / new_accum.constant(lr()) +
253 linear.constant(static_cast<T>(2) * l2());
254 auto pre_shrink = x / y;
255 var.device(d) = (linear.abs() > linear.constant(l1()))
256 .select(pre_shrink, var.constant(static_cast<T>(0)));
257
258 } else {
259 auto y = new_accum.pow(-lr_power()) / new_accum.constant(lr()) +
260 linear.constant(static_cast<T>(2) * l2());
261 auto pre_shrink = x / y;
262 var.device(d) = (linear.abs() > linear.constant(l1()))
263 .select(pre_shrink, var.constant(static_cast<T>(0)));
264 }
265 accum.device(d) += grad.square();
266 }
267};

269template <typename T>
270struct ApplyMomentum<CPUDevice, T> {
271 void operator()(const CPUDevice& d, typename TTypes<T>::Flat var,
272 typename TTypes<T>::Flat accum,
273 typename TTypes<T>::ConstScalar lr,
274 typename TTypes<T>::ConstFlat grad,
275 typename TTypes<T>::ConstScalar momentum, bool use_nesterov) {
276 accum.device(d) = accum * momentum() + grad;
277 if (use_nesterov) {
278 var.device(d) -= grad * lr() + accum * momentum() * lr();
279 } else {
280 var.device(d) -= accum * lr();
281 }
282 }
283};

285template <typename Device, typename T>
286struct ApplyAdamNonCuda {
287 void operator()(const Device& d, typename TTypes<T>::Flat var,
288 typename TTypes<T>::Flat m, typename TTypes<T>::Flat v,
289 typename TTypes<T>::ConstScalar beta1_power,
290 typename TTypes<T>::ConstScalar beta2_power,
291 typename TTypes<T>::ConstScalar lr,
292 typename TTypes<T>::ConstScalar beta1,
293 typename TTypes<T>::ConstScalar beta2,
294 typename TTypes<T>::ConstScalar epsilon,
295 typename TTypes<T>::ConstFlat grad, bool use_nesterov) {
296 const T alpha = lr() * Eigen::numext::sqrt(T(1) - beta2_power()) /
297 (T(1) - beta1_power());
298 // beta1 == μ
299 // beta2 == ν
300 // v == n
301 // var == θ
302
303 m.device(d) += (grad - m) * (T(1) - beta1());
304 v.device(d) += (grad.square() - v) * (T(1) - beta2());
305 if (use_nesterov) {
306 var.device(d) -= ((grad * (T(1) - beta1()) + beta1() * m) * alpha) /
307 (v.sqrt() + epsilon());
308 } else {
309 var.device(d) -= (m * alpha) / (v.sqrt() + epsilon());
310 }
311 }
312};
313
314#ifdef TENSORFLOW_USE_SYCL
315template <typename T>
316struct ApplyAdamSYCL {
317 void operator()(const SYCLDevice& d, typename TTypes<T>::Flat var,
318 typename TTypes<T>::Flat m, typename TTypes<T>::Flat v,
319 T beta1_power, T beta2_power, T lr, T beta1, T beta2,
320 T epsilon, typename TTypes<T>::ConstFlat grad) {
321 const T alpha =
322 lr * Eigen::numext::sqrt(T(1) - beta2_power) / (T(1) - beta1_power);
323 m.device(d) += (grad - m) * (T(1) - beta1);
324 v.device(d) += (grad.square() - v) * (T(1) - beta2);
325 var.device(d) -= (m * alpha) / (v.sqrt() + epsilon);
326 }
327};
328#endif // TENSORFLOW_USE_SYCL

333template <typename T>
334struct ApplyRMSProp<CPUDevice, T> {
335 void operator()(const CPUDevice& d, typename TTypes<T>::Flat var,
336 typename TTypes<T>::Flat ms, typename TTypes<T>::Flat mom,
337 typename TTypes<T>::ConstScalar lr,
338 typename TTypes<T>::ConstScalar rho,
339 typename TTypes<T>::ConstScalar momentum,
340 typename TTypes<T>::ConstScalar epsilon,
341 typename TTypes<T>::ConstFlat grad) {
342 ms.device(d) += (grad.square() - ms) * (static_cast<T>(1) - rho());
343 mom.device(d) =
344 mom * momentum() + (grad * lr()) / ((ms + epsilon()).sqrt());
345 var.device(d) -= mom;
346 }
347};
348
349template <typename T>
350struct ApplyCenteredRMSProp<CPUDevice, T> {
351 void operator()(const CPUDevice& d, typename TTypes<T>::Flat var,
352 typename TTypes<T>::Flat mg, typename TTypes<T>::Flat ms,
353 typename TTypes<T>::Flat mom,
354 typename TTypes<T>::ConstScalar lr,
355 typename TTypes<T>::ConstScalar rho,
356 typename TTypes<T>::ConstScalar momentum,
357 typename TTypes<T>::ConstScalar epsilon,
358 typename TTypes<T>::ConstFlat grad) {
359 ms.device(d) += (grad.square() - ms) * (static_cast<T>(1) - rho());
360 mg.device(d) += (grad - mg) * (static_cast<T>(1) - rho());
361 auto denom = (ms - mg.square()) + epsilon();
362 mom.device(d) = mom * momentum() + (grad * lr()) / denom.sqrt();
363 var.device(d) -= mom;
364 }
365};

367template <typename T>
368struct ApplyAddSign<CPUDevice, T> {
369 void operator()(const CPUDevice& d, typename TTypes<T>::Flat var,
370 typename TTypes<T>::Flat m,
371 typename TTypes<T>::ConstScalar lr,
372 typename TTypes<T>::ConstScalar alpha,
373 typename TTypes<T>::ConstScalar sign_decay,
374 typename TTypes<T>::ConstScalar beta,
375 typename TTypes<T>::ConstFlat grad) {
376 m.device(d) = m * beta() + grad * (static_cast<T>(1) - beta());
377 auto sign_gm = grad.sign() * m.sign();
378 var.device(d) -= lr() * (alpha() + sign_decay() * sign_gm) * grad;
379 }
380};
381
382template <typename T>
383struct ApplyPowerSign<CPUDevice, T> {
384 void operator()(const CPUDevice& d, typename TTypes<T>::Flat var,
385 typename TTypes<T>::Flat m,
386 typename TTypes<T>::ConstScalar lr,
387 typename TTypes<T>::ConstScalar logbase,
388 typename TTypes<T>::ConstScalar sign_decay,
389 typename TTypes<T>::ConstScalar beta,
390 typename TTypes<T>::ConstFlat grad) {
391 m.device(d) = m * beta() + grad * (static_cast<T>(1) - beta());
392 auto sign_gm = grad.sign() * m.sign();
393 auto grad_scale = (logbase() * sign_decay() * sign_gm).exp();
394 var.device(d) -= lr() * grad_scale * grad;
395 }
396};

400template <typename Device, typename T>
401class ApplyGradientDescentOp : public OpKernel {
402 public:
403 explicit ApplyGradientDescentOp(OpKernelConstruction* ctx) : OpKernel(ctx) {
404 OP_REQUIRES_OK(ctx, ctx->GetAttr("use_locking", &use_exclusive_lock_));
405 }
406
407 void Compute(OpKernelContext* ctx) override {
408 auto locks =
409 MaybeLockVariableInputMutexesInOrder(ctx, use_exclusive_lock_, {0});
410 Tensor var;
411 OP_REQUIRES_OK(ctx, GetInputTensorFromVariable<Device, T>(
412 ctx, 0, use_exclusive_lock_, false, &var));
413
414 OP_REQUIRES(
415 ctx, var.IsInitialized(),
416 errors::FailedPrecondition(
417 "Attempting to use uninitialized variables: ", requested_input(0)));
418 const Tensor& alpha = ctx->input(1);
419 OP_REQUIRES(ctx, IsLegacyScalar(alpha.shape()),
420 errors::InvalidArgument("alpha is not a scalar: ",
421 alpha.shape().DebugString()));
422 const Tensor& delta = ctx->input(2);
423 OP_REQUIRES(
424 ctx, var.shape().IsSameSize(delta.shape()),
425 errors::InvalidArgument("var and delta do not have the same shape",
426 var.shape().DebugString(), " ",
427 delta.shape().DebugString()));
428
429 const Device& device = ctx->template eigen_device<Device>();
430 functor::ApplyGradientDescent<Device, T>()(
431 device, var.flat<T>(), alpha.scalar<T>(), delta.flat<T>());
432
433 MaybeForwardRefInputToRefOutput(ctx, 0, 0);
434 }
435
436 private:
437 bool use_exclusive_lock_;
438};
439

442class ApplyGradientDescentOp<SYCLDevice, T> : public OpKernel {
443 public:
444 explicit ApplyGradientDescentOp(OpKernelConstruction* ctx) : OpKernel(ctx) {
445 OP_REQUIRES_OK(ctx, ctx->GetAttr("use_locking", &use_exclusive_lock_));
446 }
447
448 void Compute(OpKernelContext* ctx) override {
449 auto locks =
450 MaybeLockVariableInputMutexesInOrder(ctx, use_exclusive_lock_, {0});
451 Tensor var;
452 OP_REQUIRES_OK(ctx, GetInputTensorFromVariable<SYCLDevice, T>(
453 ctx, 0, use_exclusive_lock_, false, &var));
454
455 OP_REQUIRES(
456 ctx, var.IsInitialized(),
457 errors::FailedPrecondition(
458 "Attempting to use uninitialized variables: ", requested_input(0)));
459 const Tensor& alpha_dev = ctx->input(1);
460 OP_REQUIRES(ctx, IsLegacyScalar(alpha_dev.shape()),
461 errors::InvalidArgument("alpha is not a scalar: ",
462 alpha_dev.shape().DebugString()));
463 const Tensor& delta = ctx->input(2);
464 OP_REQUIRES(
465 ctx, var.shape().IsSameSize(delta.shape()),

469
470 auto device = ctx->eigen_sycl_device();

476 functor::ApplyGradientDescentSYCL<T>()(device, var.flat<T>(), alpha,

478
479 MaybeForwardRefInputToRefOutput(ctx, 0, 0);
480 }
481
482 private:
483 bool use_exclusive_lock_;
484};

534template <typename Device, typename T>
535class ApplyAdadeltaOp : public OpKernel {
536 public:
537 explicit ApplyAdadeltaOp(OpKernelConstruction* ctx) : OpKernel(ctx) {
538 OP_REQUIRES_OK(ctx, ctx->GetAttr("use_locking", &use_exclusive_lock_));
539 }
540
541 void Compute(OpKernelContext* ctx) override {
542 mutex* mu = GetTrainingVariableMutex(ctx, 0);
543 if (use_exclusive_lock_ && mu != nullptr) {
544 mutex_lock l1(*mu);
545 // Don't try to acquire a lock on the second ref as they share the same
546 // mutex.
547 //
548 // mutex_lock l2(*ctx->input_ref_mutex(1));
549 DoValidate(ctx);
550 if (!ctx->status().ok()) return;
551 DoCompute(ctx);
552 } else {
553 DoValidate(ctx);
554 if (!ctx->status().ok()) return;
555 DoCompute(ctx);
556 }
557 MaybeForwardRefInputToRefOutput(ctx, 0, 0);
558 }
559
560 private:
561 bool use_exclusive_lock_;
562
563 void DoValidate(OpKernelContext* ctx) {
564 Tensor var;
565 OP_REQUIRES_OK(ctx, GetInputTensorFromVariable<Device, T>(
566 ctx, 0, use_exclusive_lock_, false, &var));
567 Tensor accum;
568 OP_REQUIRES_OK(ctx, GetInputTensorFromVariable<Device, T>(
569 ctx, 1, use_exclusive_lock_, false, &accum));
570 Tensor accum_update;
571 OP_REQUIRES_OK(ctx, GetInputTensorFromVariable<Device, T>(
572 ctx, 2, use_exclusive_lock_, false, &accum_update));
573
574 OP_REQUIRES(
575 ctx, var.IsInitialized(),
576 errors::FailedPrecondition(
577 "Attempting to use uninitialized variables: ", requested_input(0)));
578 OP_REQUIRES(
579 ctx, accum.IsInitialized(),
580 errors::FailedPrecondition(
581 "Attempting to use uninitialized variables: ", requested_input(1)));
582 OP_REQUIRES(
583 ctx, accum_update.IsInitialized(),
584 errors::FailedPrecondition(
585 "Attempting to use uninitialized variables: ", requested_input(2)));
586
587 const Tensor& lr = ctx->input(3);
588 const Tensor& rho = ctx->input(4);
589 const Tensor& epsilon = ctx->input(5);
590 const Tensor& grad = ctx->input(6);
591
592 OP_REQUIRES(ctx, TensorShapeUtils::IsScalar(lr.shape()),
593 errors::InvalidArgument("lr is not a scalar: ",
594 lr.shape().DebugString()));
595
596 OP_REQUIRES(ctx, TensorShapeUtils::IsScalar(rho.shape()),
597 errors::InvalidArgument("rho is not a scalar: ",
598 rho.shape().DebugString()));
599
600 OP_REQUIRES(ctx, TensorShapeUtils::IsScalar(epsilon.shape()),
601 errors::InvalidArgument("epsilon is not a scalar: ",
602 epsilon.shape().DebugString()));
603
604 OP_REQUIRES(
605 ctx, var.shape().IsSameSize(accum.shape()),
606 errors::InvalidArgument("var and accum do not have the same shape",
607 var.shape().DebugString(), " ",
608 accum.shape().DebugString()));
609 OP_REQUIRES(
610 ctx, var.shape().IsSameSize(grad.shape()),
611 errors::InvalidArgument("var and grad do not have the same shape",
612 var.shape().DebugString(), " ",
613 grad.shape().DebugString()));
614 }
615
616 void DoCompute(OpKernelContext* ctx) {
617 const Device& device = ctx->template eigen_device<Device>();
618 Tensor var;
619 OP_REQUIRES_OK(ctx, GetInputTensorFromVariable<Device, T>(
620 ctx, 0, use_exclusive_lock_, false, &var));
621 Tensor accum;
622 OP_REQUIRES_OK(ctx, GetInputTensorFromVariable<Device, T>(
623 ctx, 1, use_exclusive_lock_, false, &accum));
624 Tensor accum_update;
625 OP_REQUIRES_OK(ctx, GetInputTensorFromVariable<Device, T>(
626 ctx, 2, use_exclusive_lock_, false, &accum_update));
627
628 const Tensor& lr = ctx->input(3);
629 const Tensor& rho = ctx->input(4);
630 const Tensor& epsilon = ctx->input(5);
631 const Tensor& grad = ctx->input(6);
632
633 functor::ApplyAdadelta<Device, T>()(
634 device, var.flat<T>(), accum.flat<T>(), accum_update.flat<T>(),
635 lr.scalar<T>(), rho.scalar<T>(), epsilon.scalar<T>(), grad.flat<T>());
636 }

682// Note, this op works on cpu only.
683template <typename T, typename Tindex>
684class SparseApplyAdadeltaOp : public OpKernel {
685 public:
686 explicit SparseApplyAdadeltaOp(OpKernelConstruction* ctx) : OpKernel(ctx) {
687 OP_REQUIRES_OK(ctx, ctx->GetAttr("use_locking", &use_exclusive_lock_));
688 }
689
690 void Compute(OpKernelContext* ctx) override {
691 mutex* mu = GetTrainingVariableMutex(ctx, 0);
692 // mu_accum is actually the same mutex as mu_var since currently we use a
693 // global mutex.
694 //
695 // mutex* mu_accum = ctx->input_ref_mutex(1);
696 if (use_exclusive_lock_ && mu != nullptr) {
697 mutex_lock ml(*mu);
698 DoCompute(ctx);
699 } else {
700 DoCompute(ctx);
701 }
702 }
703
704 void DoCompute(OpKernelContext* ctx) {
705 Tensor var;
706 OP_REQUIRES_OK(ctx, GetInputTensorFromVariable<CPUDevice, T>(
707 ctx, 0, use_exclusive_lock_, true, &var));
708 Tensor accum_grad;
709 OP_REQUIRES_OK(ctx, GetInputTensorFromVariable<CPUDevice, T>(
710 ctx, 1, use_exclusive_lock_, true, &accum_grad));
711 Tensor accum_update;
712 OP_REQUIRES_OK(ctx, GetInputTensorFromVariable<CPUDevice, T>(
713 ctx, 2, use_exclusive_lock_, true, &accum_update));
714 OP_REQUIRES(
715 ctx, var.IsInitialized(),
716 errors::FailedPrecondition(
717 "Attempting to use uninitialized variables: ", requested_input(0)));
718 OP_REQUIRES(
719 ctx, accum_grad.IsInitialized(),
720 errors::FailedPrecondition(
721 "Attempting to use uninitialized variables: ", requested_input(1)));
722 OP_REQUIRES(
723 ctx, accum_update.IsInitialized(),
724 errors::FailedPrecondition(
725 "Attempting to use uninitialized variables: ", requested_input(2)));
726 OP_REQUIRES(
727 ctx, var.shape().IsSameSize(accum_grad.shape()),
728 errors::InvalidArgument("var and accum_grad do not have the same shape",
729 var.shape().DebugString(), " ",
730 accum_grad.shape().DebugString()));
731 OP_REQUIRES(ctx, var.shape().IsSameSize(accum_update.shape()),
732 errors::InvalidArgument(
733 "var and accum_update do not have the same shape",
734 var.shape().DebugString(), " ",
735 accum_update.shape().DebugString()));
736 OP_REQUIRES(ctx, TensorShapeUtils::IsVectorOrHigher(var.shape()),
737 errors::InvalidArgument("var must be at least 1 dimensional"));
738
739 const Tensor& lr = ctx->input(3);
740 OP_REQUIRES(ctx, TensorShapeUtils::IsScalar(lr.shape()),
741 errors::InvalidArgument("lr is not a scalar: ",
742 lr.shape().DebugString()));
743 const Tensor& rho = ctx->input(4);
744 OP_REQUIRES(ctx, TensorShapeUtils::IsScalar(rho.shape()),
745 errors::InvalidArgument("rho is not a scalar: ",
746 rho.shape().DebugString()));
747 const Tensor& epsilon = ctx->input(5);
748 OP_REQUIRES(ctx, TensorShapeUtils::IsScalar(epsilon.shape()),
749 errors::InvalidArgument("epsilon is not a scalar: ",
750 epsilon.shape().DebugString()));
751 const Tensor& grad = ctx->input(6);
752 const Tensor& indices = ctx->input(7);
753 OP_REQUIRES(ctx, TensorShapeUtils::IsVector(indices.shape()),
754 errors::InvalidArgument("indices must be one-dimensional"));
755
756 for (int d = 1; d < var.dims(); d++) {
757 OP_REQUIRES(ctx, var.dim_size(d) == grad.dim_size(d),
758 errors::InvalidArgument(strings::StrCat(
759 "var and grad must match in dimension ", d)));
760 }
761 const Tindex N = indices.dim_size(0);
762 OP_REQUIRES(
763 ctx, grad.dim_size(0) == N,
764 errors::InvalidArgument(
765 "grad must be the same size as indices in the first dimension."));
766
767 if (N > 0) {
768 const Tindex first_dim_size = var.dim_size(0);
769 // Validate all the indices are in range
770 auto indices_vec = indices.vec<Tindex>();
771 for (Tindex i = 0; i < N; i++) {
772 const Tindex index = indices_vec(i);
773 OP_REQUIRES(ctx, index >= 0 && index < first_dim_size,
774 errors::InvalidArgument(
775 strings::StrCat("Index ", index, " at offset ", i,
776 " in indices is out of range")));
777 }
778
779 auto var_flat = var.flat_outer_dims<T>();
780 auto accum_grad_flat = accum_grad.flat_outer_dims<T>();
781 auto accum_update_flat = accum_update.flat_outer_dims<T>();
782 auto grad_flat = grad.flat_outer_dims<T>();
783 const T lr_scalar = lr.scalar<T>()();
784 const T rho_scalar = rho.scalar<T>()();
785 const T epsilon_scalar = epsilon.scalar<T>()();
786
787 for (Tindex i = 0; i < N; i++) {
788 const Tindex index = indices_vec(i);
789 auto accum_ = accum_grad_flat.template chip<0>(index);
790 auto accum_update_ = accum_update_flat.template chip<0>(index);
791 auto grad_ = grad_flat.template chip<0>(i);
792
793 accum_ = accum_ * accum_.constant(rho_scalar) +
794 grad_.square() * grad_.constant(T(1) - rho_scalar);
795 const auto update =
796 (accum_update_ + accum_update_.constant(epsilon_scalar)).sqrt() *
797 (accum_ + accum_.constant(epsilon_scalar)).rsqrt() * grad_;
798 auto v = var_flat.template chip<0>(index);
799 v -= update * update.constant(lr_scalar);
800 accum_update_ =
801 accum_update_ * accum_update_.constant(rho_scalar) +
802 update.square() * update.constant(static_cast<T>(1) - rho_scalar);
803 }
804 }
805
806 MaybeForwardRefInputToRefOutput(ctx, 0, 0);
807 }
808
809 private:
810 bool use_exclusive_lock_;
811};

905// Note, this op works on cpu only.
906template <typename T, typename Tindex>
907class SparseApplyProximalGradientDescentOp : public OpKernel {
908 public:
909 explicit SparseApplyProximalGradientDescentOp(OpKernelConstruction* ctx)
910 : OpKernel(ctx) {
911 OP_REQUIRES_OK(ctx, ctx->GetAttr("use_locking", &use_exclusive_lock_));
912 }
913
914 void Compute(OpKernelContext* ctx) override NO_THREAD_SAFETY_ANALYSIS {
915 auto locks =
916 MaybeLockVariableInputMutexesInOrder(ctx, use_exclusive_lock_, {0});
917 Tensor var;
918 OP_REQUIRES_OK(ctx, GetInputTensorFromVariable<CPUDevice, T>(
919 ctx, 0, use_exclusive_lock_, true, &var));
920 OP_REQUIRES(ctx, TensorShapeUtils::IsVectorOrHigher(var.shape()),
921 errors::InvalidArgument("var must be at least 1 dimensional"));
922
923 const Tensor& lr = ctx->input(1);
924 OP_REQUIRES(ctx, IsLegacyScalar(lr.shape()),
925 errors::InvalidArgument("lr is not a scalar: ",
926 lr.shape().DebugString()));
927 const Tensor& l1 = ctx->input(2);
928 OP_REQUIRES(
929 ctx, TensorShapeUtils::IsScalar(l1.shape()),
930 errors::InvalidArgument("l1 regularization strength is not a scalar: ",
931 l1.shape().DebugString()));
932 const Tensor& l2 = ctx->input(3);
933 OP_REQUIRES(
934 ctx, TensorShapeUtils::IsScalar(l2.shape()),
935 errors::InvalidArgument("l2 regularization strength is not a scalar: ",
936 l2.shape().DebugString()));
937
938 const Tensor& grad = ctx->input(4);
939 const Tensor& indices = ctx->input(5);
940 OP_REQUIRES(ctx, TensorShapeUtils::IsVector(indices.shape()),
941 errors::InvalidArgument("indices must be one-dimensional"));
942
943 int64 inner_dim = 1;
944 for (int d = 1; d < var.dims(); d++) {
945 OP_REQUIRES(ctx, var.dim_size(d) == grad.dim_size(d),
946 errors::InvalidArgument(strings::StrCat(
947 "var and grad must match in dimension ", d)));
948 inner_dim *= grad.dim_size(d);
949 }
950 const Tindex N = indices.dim_size(0);
951 OP_REQUIRES(
952 ctx, grad.dim_size(0) == N,
953 errors::InvalidArgument(
954 "grad must be the same size as indices in the first dimension."));
955 OP_REQUIRES(ctx, inner_dim > 0,
956 errors::InvalidArgument(
957 "Inner dimension should be greater than zero."));
958
959 if (N > 0) {
960 if (inner_dim > 1) {
961 const Tindex first_dim_size = var.dim_size(0);
962 auto indices_vec = indices.vec<Tindex>();
963 auto var_flat = var.flat_outer_dims<T>();
964 auto grad_flat = grad.flat_outer_dims<T>();
965 T lr_scalar = lr.scalar<T>()();
966 T l1_scalar = l1.scalar<T>()();
967 T l2_scalar = l2.scalar<T>()();
968
969 // TODO(xbing): extract the common logic for the Fobos update.
970 for (Tindex i = 0; i < N; i++) {
971 const Tindex index = internal::SubtleMustCopy(indices_vec(i));
972 OP_REQUIRES(ctx, FastBoundsCheck(index, first_dim_size),
973 errors::InvalidArgument(
974 strings::StrCat("Index ", index, " at offset ", i,
975 " in indices is out of range")));
976 auto g = grad_flat.template chip<0>(i);
977 auto v = var_flat.template chip<0>(index);
978 // compute learning_rate for current step.
979 auto learning_rate = v.constant(lr_scalar);
980 auto prox_v = v;
981 // v = w - g * learning_rate.
982 prox_v -= g * learning_rate;
983 if (l1_scalar > 0) {
984 // compute sign(v) * max(|v|, 0)
985 v = prox_v.sign() *
986 (prox_v.abs() - learning_rate * prox_v.constant(l1_scalar))
987 .cwiseMax(static_cast<T>(0.0)) /
988 (v.constant(1.0) + v.constant(l2_scalar) * learning_rate);
989 } else {
990 v = prox_v /
991 (v.constant(1.0) + v.constant(l2_scalar) * learning_rate);
992 }
993 }
994 } else {
995 auto indices_vec = indices.vec<Tindex>();
996 auto var_flat = var.flat<T>();
997 auto grad_flat = grad.flat<T>();
998 T lr_scalar = lr.scalar<T>()();
999 T l1_scalar = l1.scalar<T>()();
1000 T l2_scalar = l2.scalar<T>()();
1001 const Tindex first_dim_size = var_flat.size();
1002
1003 for (Tindex i = 0; i < N; i++) {
1004 const Tindex index = internal::SubtleMustCopy(indices_vec(i));
1005 OP_REQUIRES(ctx, FastBoundsCheck(index, first_dim_size),
1006 errors::InvalidArgument(
1007 strings::StrCat("Index ", index, " at offset ", i,
1008 " in indices is out of range")));
1009 const T& g = grad_flat(i);
1010 auto learning_rate = lr_scalar;
1011 auto prox_v = var_flat(index);
1012 prox_v -= learning_rate * g;
1013 if (l1_scalar > 0) {
1014 var_flat(index) =
1015 sgn(prox_v) *
1016 std::max(std::abs(prox_v) - learning_rate * l1_scalar,
1017 static_cast<T>(0.0)) /
1018 (1.0 + l2_scalar * learning_rate);
1019 } else {
1020 var_flat(index) = prox_v / (1.0 + l2_scalar * learning_rate);
1021 }
1022 }
1023 }
1024 }
1025
1026 MaybeForwardRefInputToRefOutput(ctx, 0, 0);
1027 }
1028
1029 private:
1030 bool use_exclusive_lock_;
1031};

1187 l2.scalar<T>()() >= static_cast<T>(0),

1189 "non-negative scalar: ",
1190 l2.shape().DebugString()));
1191 const Tensor& grad = ctx->input(5);

1227template <typename T>
1228inline T FtrlCompute(const T& accum, const T& linear, const T& lr, const T& l1,
1229 const T& l2, const T& lr_power) {
1230 T quadratic;
1231 if (lr_power == static_cast<T>(-0.5)) {
1232 quadratic = Eigen::numext::sqrt(accum) / lr + static_cast<T>(2) * l2;
1233 } else {
1234 quadratic =
1235 Eigen::numext::pow(accum, -lr_power) / lr + static_cast<T>(2) * l2;
1236 }
1237 auto l1_reg_adjust = std::max(std::min(linear, l1), -l1);
1238 return (l1_reg_adjust - linear) / quadratic;
1239}
1240} // namespace

1243template <typename T, typename Tindex>
1244class SparseApplyAdagradOp : public OpKernel {
1245 public:
1246 explicit SparseApplyAdagradOp(OpKernelConstruction* ctx) : OpKernel(ctx) {
1247 OP_REQUIRES_OK(ctx, ctx->GetAttr("use_locking", &use_exclusive_lock_));
1248 }
1249
1250 void Compute(OpKernelContext* ctx) override NO_THREAD_SAFETY_ANALYSIS {
1251 auto locks =
1252 MaybeLockVariableInputMutexesInOrder(ctx, use_exclusive_lock_, {0, 1});
1253 Tensor var;
1254 OP_REQUIRES_OK(ctx, GetInputTensorFromVariable<CPUDevice, T>(
1255 ctx, 0, use_exclusive_lock_, true, &var));
1256 Tensor accum;
1257 OP_REQUIRES_OK(ctx, GetInputTensorFromVariable<CPUDevice, T>(
1258 ctx, 1, use_exclusive_lock_, true, &accum));
1259 OP_REQUIRES(
1260 ctx, var.IsInitialized(),
1261 errors::FailedPrecondition(
1262 "Attempting to use uninitialized variables: ", requested_input(0)));
1263 OP_REQUIRES(
1264 ctx, accum.IsInitialized(),
1265 errors::FailedPrecondition(
1266 "Attempting to use uninitialized variables: ", requested_input(1)));
1267 OP_REQUIRES(
1268 ctx, var.shape().IsSameSize(accum.shape()),
1269 errors::InvalidArgument("var and accum do not have the same shape",
1270 var.shape().DebugString(), " ",
1271 accum.shape().DebugString()));
1272 OP_REQUIRES(ctx, TensorShapeUtils::IsVectorOrHigher(var.shape()),
1273 errors::InvalidArgument("var must be at least 1 dimensional"));
1274
1275 const Tensor& lr = ctx->input(2);
1276 OP_REQUIRES(ctx, IsLegacyScalar(lr.shape()),
1277 errors::InvalidArgument("lr is not a scalar: ",
1278 lr.shape().DebugString()));
1279 const Tensor& grad = ctx->input(3);
1280 const Tensor& indices = ctx->input(4);
1281 OP_REQUIRES(ctx, TensorShapeUtils::IsVector(indices.shape()),
1282 errors::InvalidArgument("indices must be one-dimensional"));
1283
1284 int64 inner_dim = 1;
1285 for (int d = 1; d < var.dims(); d++) {
1286 OP_REQUIRES(ctx, var.dim_size(d) == grad.dim_size(d),
1287 errors::InvalidArgument(strings::StrCat(
1288 "var and grad must match in dimension ", d)));
1289 inner_dim *= grad.dim_size(d);
1290 }
1291 const Tindex N = indices.dim_size(0);
1292 OP_REQUIRES(
1293 ctx, grad.dim_size(0) == N,
1294 errors::InvalidArgument(
1295 "grad must be the same size as indices in the first dimension."));
1296
1297 OP_REQUIRES(ctx, inner_dim > 0,
1298 errors::InvalidArgument(
1299 "Inner dimension should be greater than zero."));
1300
1301 if (N > 0) {
1302 if (inner_dim > 1) {
1303 const Tindex first_dim_size = var.dim_size(0);
1304 auto indices_vec = indices.vec<Tindex>();
1305 auto var_flat = var.flat_outer_dims<T>();
1306 auto accum_flat = accum.flat_outer_dims<T>();
1307 auto grad_flat = grad.flat_outer_dims<T>();
1308 T lr_scalar = lr.scalar<T>()();
1309
1310 // Note(yonghui): It might be worth multi-threading square() and
1311 // rsqrt().
1312 for (Tindex i = 0; i < N; i++) {
1313 const Tindex index = internal::SubtleMustCopy(indices_vec(i));
1314 OP_REQUIRES(ctx, FastBoundsCheck(index, first_dim_size),
1315 errors::InvalidArgument(
1316 strings::StrCat("Index ", index, " at offset ", i,
1317 " in indices is out of range")));
1318 auto a = accum_flat.template chip<0>(index);
1319 auto g = grad_flat.template chip<0>(i);
1320 auto v = var_flat.template chip<0>(index);
1321 a += g.square();
1322 v -= g.constant(lr_scalar) * g * a.rsqrt();
1323 }
1324 } else {
1325 auto indices_vec = indices.vec<Tindex>();
1326 auto var_flat = var.flat<T>();
1327 auto accum_flat = accum.flat<T>();
1328 auto grad_flat = grad.flat<T>();
1329 T lr_scalar = lr.scalar<T>()();
1330 const Tindex first_dim_size = accum_flat.size();
1331
1332 for (Tindex i = 0; i < N; i++) {
1333 const Tindex index = internal::SubtleMustCopy(indices_vec(i));
1334 OP_REQUIRES(ctx, FastBoundsCheck(index, first_dim_size),
1335 errors::InvalidArgument(
1336 strings::StrCat("Index ", index, " at offset ", i,
1337 " in indices is out of range")));
1338 T& a = accum_flat(index);
1339 const T& g = grad_flat(i);
1340 a += g * g;
1341 var_flat(index) -= lr_scalar * g / Eigen::numext::sqrt(a);
1342 }
1343 }
1344 }
1345
1346 MaybeForwardRefInputToRefOutput(ctx, 0, 0);
1347 }
1348
1349 private:
1350 bool use_exclusive_lock_;
1351};

1377template <typename T, typename Tindex>
1378class SparseApplyProximalAdagradOp : public OpKernel {
1379 public:
1380 explicit SparseApplyProximalAdagradOp(OpKernelConstruction* ctx)
1381 : OpKernel(ctx) {
1382 OP_REQUIRES_OK(ctx, ctx->GetAttr("use_locking", &use_exclusive_lock_));
1383 }
1384
1385 void Compute(OpKernelContext* ctx) override NO_THREAD_SAFETY_ANALYSIS {
1386 auto locks =
1387 MaybeLockVariableInputMutexesInOrder(ctx, use_exclusive_lock_, {0, 1});
1388 Tensor var;
1389 OP_REQUIRES_OK(ctx, GetInputTensorFromVariable<CPUDevice, T>(
1390 ctx, 0, use_exclusive_lock_, true, &var));
1391 Tensor accum;
1392 OP_REQUIRES_OK(ctx, GetInputTensorFromVariable<CPUDevice, T>(
1393 ctx, 1, use_exclusive_lock_, true, &accum));
1394 OP_REQUIRES(
1395 ctx, var.IsInitialized(),
1396 errors::FailedPrecondition(
1397 "Attempting to use uninitialized variables: ", requested_input(0)));
1398 OP_REQUIRES(
1399 ctx, accum.IsInitialized(),
1400 errors::FailedPrecondition(
1401 "Attempting to use uninitialized variables: ", requested_input(1)));
1402 OP_REQUIRES(
1403 ctx, var.shape().IsSameSize(accum.shape()),
1404 errors::InvalidArgument("var and accum do not have the same shape",
1405 var.shape().DebugString(), " ",
1406 accum.shape().DebugString()));
1407 OP_REQUIRES(ctx, TensorShapeUtils::IsVectorOrHigher(var.shape()),
1408 errors::InvalidArgument("var must be at least 1 dimensional"));
1409
1410 const Tensor& lr = ctx->input(2);
1411 OP_REQUIRES(ctx,
1412 TensorShapeUtils::IsScalar(lr.shape()) &&
1413 lr.scalar<T>()() > static_cast<T>(0),
1414 errors::InvalidArgument("lr is not a positive scalar: ",
1415 lr.shape().DebugString()));
1416 const Tensor& l1 = ctx->input(3);
1417 OP_REQUIRES(ctx,
1418 TensorShapeUtils::IsScalar(l1.shape()) &&
1419 l1.scalar<T>()() >= static_cast<T>(0),
1420 errors::InvalidArgument("l1 regularization strength is not a "
1421 "non-negative scalar: ",
1422 l1.shape().DebugString()));
1423 const Tensor& l2 = ctx->input(4);
1424 OP_REQUIRES(ctx,
1425 TensorShapeUtils::IsScalar(l2.shape()) &&
1426 l2.scalar<T>()() >= static_cast<T>(0),
1427 errors::InvalidArgument("l2 regularization strength is not a "
1428 "non-negative scalar: ",
1429 l2.shape().DebugString()));
1430
1431 const Tensor& grad = ctx->input(5);
1432 const Tensor& indices = ctx->input(6);
1433 OP_REQUIRES(ctx, TensorShapeUtils::IsVector(indices.shape()),
1434 errors::InvalidArgument("indices must be one-dimensional"));
1435
1436 int64 inner_dim = 1;
1437 for (int d = 1; d < var.dims(); d++) {
1438 OP_REQUIRES(ctx, var.dim_size(d) == grad.dim_size(d),
1439 errors::InvalidArgument(strings::StrCat(
1440 "var and grad must match in dimension ", d)));
1441 inner_dim *= grad.dim_size(d);
1442 }
1443 const Tindex N = indices.dim_size(0);
1444 OP_REQUIRES(
1445 ctx, grad.dim_size(0) == N,
1446 errors::InvalidArgument(
1447 "grad must be the same size as indices in the first dimension."));
1448
1449 OP_REQUIRES(ctx, inner_dim > 0,
1450 errors::InvalidArgument(
1451 "Inner dimension should be greater than zero."));
1452
1453 if (N > 0) {
1454 if (inner_dim > 1) {
1455 const Tindex first_dim_size = var.dim_size(0);
1456 auto indices_vec = indices.vec<Tindex>();
1457 auto var_flat = var.flat_outer_dims<T>();
1458 auto accum_flat = accum.flat_outer_dims<T>();
1459 auto grad_flat = grad.flat_outer_dims<T>();
1460 T lr_scalar = lr.scalar<T>()();
1461 T l1_scalar = l1.scalar<T>()();
1462 T l2_scalar = l2.scalar<T>()();
1463
1464 for (Tindex i = 0; i < N; i++) {
1465 const Tindex index = internal::SubtleMustCopy(indices_vec(i));
1466 OP_REQUIRES(ctx, FastBoundsCheck(index, first_dim_size),
1467 errors::InvalidArgument(
1468 strings::StrCat("Index ", index, " at offset ", i,
1469 " in indices is out of range")));
1470 auto a = accum_flat.template chip<0>(index);
1471 auto g = grad_flat.template chip<0>(i);
1472 auto v = var_flat.template chip<0>(index);
1473 a += g.square();
1474 // compute learning_rate for current step.
1475 auto learning_rate = a.constant(lr_scalar) * a.rsqrt();
1476 auto prox_v = v;
1477 // v = w - g * learning_rate.
1478 prox_v -= g * learning_rate;
1479 if (l1_scalar > 0) {
1480 // compute sign(v) * max(|v|, 0)
1481 v = prox_v.sign() *
1482 (prox_v.abs() - learning_rate * prox_v.constant(l1_scalar))
1483 .cwiseMax(static_cast<T>(0.0)) /
1484 (v.constant(1.0) + v.constant(l2_scalar) * learning_rate);
1485 } else {
1486 v = prox_v /
1487 (v.constant(1.0) + v.constant(l2_scalar) * learning_rate);
1488 }
1489 }
1490 } else {
1491 auto indices_vec = indices.vec<Tindex>();
1492 auto var_flat = var.flat<T>();
1493 auto accum_flat = accum.flat<T>();
1494 auto grad_flat = grad.flat<T>();
1495 T lr_scalar = lr.scalar<T>()();
1496 T l1_scalar = l1.scalar<T>()();
1497 T l2_scalar = l2.scalar<T>()();
1498 const Tindex first_dim_size = accum_flat.size();
1499
1500 for (Tindex i = 0; i < N; i++) {
1501 const Tindex index = internal::SubtleMustCopy(indices_vec(i));
1502 OP_REQUIRES(ctx, FastBoundsCheck(index, first_dim_size),
1503 errors::InvalidArgument(
1504 strings::StrCat("Index ", index, " at offset ", i,
1505 " in indices is out of range")));
1506 T& a = accum_flat(index);
1507 const T& g = grad_flat(i);
1508 a += g * g;
1509 auto learning_rate = lr_scalar / std::sqrt(a);
1510 auto prox_v = var_flat(index);
1511 prox_v -= learning_rate * g;
1512 if (l1_scalar > 0) {
1513 var_flat(index) =
1514 sgn(prox_v) *
1515 std::max(std::abs(prox_v) - learning_rate * l1_scalar,
1516 static_cast<T>(0.0)) /
1517 (1.0 + l2_scalar * learning_rate);
1518 } else {
1519 var_flat(index) = prox_v / (1.0 + l2_scalar * learning_rate);
1520 }
1521 }
1522 }
1523 }
1524
1525 MaybeForwardRefInputToRefOutput(ctx, 0, 0);
1526 }
1527
1528 private:
1529 bool use_exclusive_lock_;
1530};

1732 const Tindex N = indices.dim_size(0);
1733 OP_REQUIRES(
1734 ctx, grad.dim_size(0) == N,
1735 errors::InvalidArgument(
1736 "grad must be the same size as indices in the first dimension."));
1737
1738 OP_REQUIRES(ctx, inner_dim > 0,
1739 errors::InvalidArgument(
1740 "Inner dimension should be greater than zero."));
1741
1742 // AdagradDA update:
1743 // Let g to be gradient accumulator, gg to be gradient squared accumulator,
1744 // T be the global step, lr is the learning rate, and k the initial
1745 // gradient squared accumulator value.
1746 // w = \dfrac{sign(-g)*lr*|g - l1*T|_{+}}{l2*T*lr + \sqrt{k+gg})}
1747 if (N > 0) {
1748 if (inner_dim > 1) {
1749 const Tindex first_dim_size = var.dim_size(0);
1750 auto indices_vec = indices.vec<Tindex>();
1751 auto var_flat = var.flat_outer_dims<T>();
1752 auto gradient_accum_flat = gradient_accum.flat_outer_dims<T>();
1753 auto gradient_squared_accum_flat =
1754 gradient_squared_accum.flat_outer_dims<T>();
1755 auto grad_flat = grad.flat_outer_dims<T>();
1756 T lr_scalar = lr.scalar<T>()();
1757 T global_step_scalar = global_step.scalar<int64>()();
1758 T l1_scalar = l1.scalar<T>()();
1759 T l2_scalar = l2.scalar<T>()();
1760 const double gs_lr = global_step_scalar * lr_scalar;
1761
1762 for (Tindex i = 0; i < N; i++) {
1763 const Tindex index = internal::SubtleMustCopy(indices_vec(i));
1764 OP_REQUIRES(ctx, FastBoundsCheck(index, first_dim_size),
1765 errors::InvalidArgument(
1766 strings::StrCat("Index ", index, " at offset ", i,
1767 " in indices is out of range")));
1768 auto ga = gradient_accum_flat.template chip<0>(index);
1769 auto da = gradient_squared_accum_flat.template chip<0>(index);
1770 auto g = grad_flat.template chip<0>(i);
1771 auto v = var_flat.template chip<0>(index);
1772 ga += g;
1773 da += g.square();
1774 if (l1_scalar > 0) {
1775 v = ga.constant(-1.0) * ga.sign() *
1776 ((ga.abs() / ga.constant(global_step_scalar)) -
1777 ga.constant(l1_scalar))
1778 .cwiseMax(static_cast<T>(0.0)) /
1779 (v.constant(l2_scalar) + da.sqrt() / v.constant(gs_lr));
1780 } else {
1781 v = ga.constant(-1.0) * (ga / ga.constant(global_step_scalar)) /
1782 (v.constant(l2_scalar) + da.sqrt() / v.constant(gs_lr));
1783 }
1784 }
1785 } else {
1786 auto indices_vec = indices.vec<Tindex>();
1787 auto var_flat = var.flat<T>();
1788 auto gradient_accum_flat = gradient_accum.flat<T>();
1789 auto gradient_squared_accum_flat = gradient_squared_accum.flat<T>();
1790 auto grad_flat = grad.flat<T>();
1791 const double lr_scalar = lr.scalar<T>()();
1792 const int64 global_step_scalar = global_step.scalar<int64>()();
1793 const double l1_scalar = l1.scalar<T>()();
1794 const double l2_scalar = l2.scalar<T>()();
1795 const Tindex first_dim_size = var_flat.size();
1796 const double gs_l1 = global_step_scalar * l1_scalar;
1797 const double gs_l2_lr = global_step_scalar * l2_scalar * lr_scalar;
1798
1799 for (Tindex i = 0; i < N; i++) {
1800 const Tindex index = internal::SubtleMustCopy(indices_vec(i));
1801 OP_REQUIRES(ctx, FastBoundsCheck(index, first_dim_size),
1802 errors::InvalidArgument(
1803 strings::StrCat("Index ", index, " at offset ", i,
1804 " in indices is out of range")));
1805 T& ga = gradient_accum_flat(index);
1806 T& da = gradient_squared_accum_flat(index);
1807 const double g = grad_flat(i);
1808 ga += g;
1809 da += g * g;
1810 if (l1_scalar > 0) {
1811 var_flat(index) = sgn(-ga) * lr_scalar *
1812 std::max((std::abs(ga) - gs_l1), 0.0) /
1813 (gs_l2_lr + std::sqrt(da));
1814 } else {
1815 var_flat(index) = (-ga * lr_scalar) / (gs_l2_lr + std::sqrt(da));
1816 }
1817 }
1818 }
1819 }
1820
1821 MaybeForwardRefInputToRefOutput(ctx, 0, 0);
1822 }
1823
1824 private:
1825 bool use_exclusive_lock_;
1826};

2041 linear.shape().DebugString()));
2042 OP_REQUIRES(ctx, TensorShapeUtils::IsVectorOrHigher(var.shape()),

2047 OP_REQUIRES(ctx, TensorShapeUtils::IsVector(indices.shape()),
2048 errors::InvalidArgument("indices must be one-dimensional"));

2051 OP_REQUIRES(ctx,

2059 TensorShapeUtils::IsScalar(l1.shape()) &&
2060 l1.scalar<T>()() >= static_cast<T>(0),
2061 errors::InvalidArgument("l1 regularization strength is not a "
2062 "non-negative scalar: ",
2063 l1.shape().DebugString()));
2064 const Tensor& l2 = ctx->input(7);
2065 OP_REQUIRES(ctx,
2066 TensorShapeUtils::IsScalar(l2.shape()) &&
2067 l2.scalar<T>()() >= static_cast<T>(0),
2068 errors::InvalidArgument("l2 regularization strength is not a "
2069 "non-negative scalar: ",
2070 l2.shape().DebugString()));
2071 const int lr_power_index = has_l2_shrinkage ? 9 : 8;
2072 const Tensor& lr_power = ctx->input(lr_power_index);
2073 OP_REQUIRES(ctx,
2074 TensorShapeUtils::IsScalar(lr_power.shape()) &&
2075 lr_power.scalar<T>()() <= static_cast<T>(0),
2076 errors::InvalidArgument("lr_power is not a "
2077 "non-positive scalar: ",

2080 for (int d = 1; d < var.dims(); d++) {

2092 OP_REQUIRES(ctx, inner_dim > 0,
2093 errors::InvalidArgument(
2094 "Inner dimension should be greater than zero."));

2101 TensorShapeUtils::IsScalar(l2_shrinkage->shape()) &&
2102 l2_shrinkage->scalar<T>()() >= static_cast<T>(0),

2104 "is not a non-negative scalar: ",
2105 l2_shrinkage->shape().DebugString()));
2106 }
2107
2108 if (N > 0) {
2109 if (inner_dim > 1) {
2110 const Tindex first_dim_size = var.dim_size(0);
2111 auto indices_vec = indices.vec<Tindex>();
2112 auto var_flat = var.flat_outer_dims<T>();
2113 auto accum_flat = accum.flat_outer_dims<T>();
2114 auto linear_flat = linear.flat_outer_dims<T>();
2115 auto grad_flat = grad.flat_outer_dims<T>();
2116 T lr_scalar = lr.scalar<T>()();
2117 T l1_scalar = l1.scalar<T>()();
2118 T l2_scalar = l2.scalar<T>()();
2119 T l2_shrinkage_scalar;
2120 if (has_l2_shrinkage) {
2121 l2_shrinkage_scalar = l2_shrinkage->scalar<T>()();
2122 }
2123 T lr_power_scalar = lr_power.scalar<T>()();
2124
2125 for (Tindex i = 0; i < N; i++) {
2126 const Tindex index = internal::SubtleMustCopy(indices_vec(i));
2127 OP_REQUIRES(ctx, FastBoundsCheck(index, first_dim_size),
2128 errors::InvalidArgument(
2129 strings::StrCat("Index ", index, " at offset ", i,
2130 " in indices is out of range")));
2131 auto accum = accum_flat.template chip<0>(index);
2132 auto linear = linear_flat.template chip<0>(index);
2133 auto grad = grad_flat.template chip<0>(i);
2134 auto var = var_flat.template chip<0>(index);
2135
2136// Use a macro to implement the computation here due to the templating of the
2137// eigen tensor library.
2138#define COMPUTE_FTRL(grad_to_use) \
2139 auto new_accum = accum + grad_to_use.square(); \
2140 if (lr_power_scalar == static_cast<T>(-0.5)) { \
2141 linear += \
2142 grad_to_use - (new_accum.sqrt() - accum.sqrt()) / lr_scalar * var; \
2143 } else { \
2144 linear += grad_to_use - (new_accum.pow(-lr_power_scalar) - \
2145 accum.pow(-lr_power_scalar)) / \
2146 lr_scalar * var; \
2147 } \
2148 auto l1_reg_adjust = linear.cwiseMin(l1_scalar).cwiseMax(-l1_scalar); \
2149 auto x = l1_reg_adjust - linear; \
2150 if (lr_power_scalar == static_cast<T>(-0.5)) { \
2151 auto y = new_accum.sqrt() / new_accum.constant(lr_scalar) + \
2152 linear.constant(static_cast<T>(2) * l2_scalar); \
2153 var = x / y; \
2154 } else { \
2155 auto y = new_accum.pow(-lr_power_scalar) / new_accum.constant(lr_scalar) + \
2156 linear.constant(static_cast<T>(2) * l2_scalar); \
2157 var = x / y; \
2158 } \
2159 accum += grad_to_use.square();
2160
2161 if (has_l2_shrinkage) {
2162 auto grad_with_shrinkage =
2163 grad + static_cast<T>(2) * l2_shrinkage_scalar * var;
2164 COMPUTE_FTRL(grad_with_shrinkage);
2165 } else {
2166 COMPUTE_FTRL(grad);
2167 }
2168 }
2169#undef COMPUTE_FTRL
2170 } else {
2171 T lr_scalar = lr.scalar<T>()();
2172 T l1_scalar = l1.scalar<T>()();
2173 T l2_scalar = l2.scalar<T>()();
2174 T lr_power_scalar = lr_power.scalar<T>()();
2175 T l2_shrinkage_scalar;
2176 if (has_l2_shrinkage) {
2177 l2_shrinkage_scalar = l2_shrinkage->scalar<T>()();
2178 }
2179
2180 auto indices_vec = indices.vec<Tindex>();
2181 auto var_flat = var.flat<T>();
2182 auto accum_flat = accum.flat<T>();
2183 auto linear_flat = linear.flat<T>();
2184 auto grad_flat = grad.flat<T>();
2185 const Tindex first_dim_size = accum_flat.size();
2186
2187 for (Tindex i = 0; i < N; i++) {
2188 const Tindex index = internal::SubtleMustCopy(indices_vec(i));
2189 OP_REQUIRES(ctx, FastBoundsCheck(index, first_dim_size),
2190 errors::InvalidArgument(
2191 strings::StrCat("Index ", index, " at offset ", i,
2192 " in indices is out of range")));
2193 T& a = accum_flat(index);
2194 T& l = linear_flat(index);
2195 T& v = var_flat(index);
2196 T g;
2197 if (has_l2_shrinkage) {
2198 g = grad_flat(i) +
2199 (static_cast<T>(2) * l2_shrinkage_scalar * var_flat(i));
2200 } else {
2201 g = grad_flat(i);
2202 }
2203
2204 T updated_a = a + g * g;
2205 using Eigen::numext::pow;
2206 T sigma = pow(updated_a, -lr_power_scalar) - pow(a, -lr_power_scalar);
2207 sigma /= lr_scalar;
2208 T updated_l = l + g - sigma * v;
2209 v = FtrlCompute(updated_a, updated_l, lr_scalar, l1_scalar, l2_scalar,
2210 lr_power_scalar);
2211 a = updated_a;
2212 l = updated_l;
2213 }
2214 }
2215 }
2216
2217 MaybeForwardRefInputToRefOutput(ctx, 0, 0);
2218 }
2219
2220 private:
2221 bool use_exclusive_lock_;
2222};

2374// Note, this op works on cpu only.
2375template <typename T, typename Tindex>
2376class SparseApplyMomentumOp : public OpKernel {
2377 public:
2378 explicit SparseApplyMomentumOp(OpKernelConstruction* ctx) : OpKernel(ctx) {
2379 OP_REQUIRES_OK(ctx, ctx->GetAttr("use_locking", &use_exclusive_lock_));
2380 OP_REQUIRES_OK(ctx, ctx->GetAttr("use_nesterov", &use_nesterov_));
2381 }
2382
2383 void Compute(OpKernelContext* ctx) override NO_THREAD_SAFETY_ANALYSIS {
2384 auto locks =
2385 MaybeLockVariableInputMutexesInOrder(ctx, use_exclusive_lock_, {0, 1});
2386
2387 Tensor var;
2388 OP_REQUIRES_OK(ctx, GetInputTensorFromVariable<CPUDevice, T>(
2389 ctx, 0, use_exclusive_lock_, true, &var));
2390 Tensor accum;
2391 OP_REQUIRES_OK(ctx, GetInputTensorFromVariable<CPUDevice, T>(
2392 ctx, 1, use_exclusive_lock_, true, &accum));
2393 OP_REQUIRES(
2394 ctx, var.IsInitialized(),
2395 errors::FailedPrecondition(
2396 "Attempting to use uninitialized variables: ", requested_input(0)));
2397 OP_REQUIRES(
2398 ctx, accum.IsInitialized(),
2399 errors::FailedPrecondition(
2400 "Attempting to use uninitialized variables: ", requested_input(1)));
2401 OP_REQUIRES(
2402 ctx, var.shape().IsSameSize(accum.shape()),
2403 errors::InvalidArgument("var and accum do not have the same shape",
2404 var.shape().DebugString(), " ",
2405 accum.shape().DebugString()));
2406 OP_REQUIRES(ctx, TensorShapeUtils::IsVectorOrHigher(var.shape()),
2407 errors::InvalidArgument("var must be at least 1 dimensional"));
2408
2409 const Tensor& lr = ctx->input(2);
2410 OP_REQUIRES(ctx, TensorShapeUtils::IsScalar(lr.shape()),
2411 errors::InvalidArgument("lr is not a scalar : ",
2412 lr.shape().DebugString()));
2413 const Tensor& grad = ctx->input(3);
2414 const Tensor& indices = ctx->input(4);
2415 OP_REQUIRES(ctx, TensorShapeUtils::IsVector(indices.shape()),
2416 errors::InvalidArgument("indices must be one-dimensional"));
2417
2418 for (int d = 1; d < var.dims(); d++) {
2419 OP_REQUIRES(ctx, var.dim_size(d) == grad.dim_size(d),
2420 errors::InvalidArgument(strings::StrCat(
2421 "var and grad must match in dimension ", d)));
2422 }
2423 const Tindex N = indices.dim_size(0);
2424 OP_REQUIRES(
2425 ctx, grad.dim_size(0) == N,
2426 errors::InvalidArgument(
2427 "grad must be the same size as indices in the first dimension."));
2428
2429 const Tensor& momentum = ctx->input(5);
2430 OP_REQUIRES(ctx, TensorShapeUtils::IsScalar(momentum.shape()),
2431 errors::InvalidArgument("momentum is not a scalar: ",
2432 momentum.shape().DebugString()));
2433
2434 if (N > 0) {
2435 const Tindex first_dim_size = var.dim_size(0);
2436 auto indices_vec = indices.vec<Tindex>();
2437 auto var_flat = var.flat_outer_dims<T>();
2438 auto accum_flat = accum.flat_outer_dims<T>();
2439 auto grad_flat = grad.flat_outer_dims<T>();
2440 T lr_scalar = lr.scalar<T>()();
2441 T momentum_scalar = momentum.scalar<T>()();
2442
2443 for (Tindex i = 0; i < N; i++) {
2444 const Tindex index = internal::SubtleMustCopy(indices_vec(i));
2445 OP_REQUIRES(ctx, FastBoundsCheck(index, first_dim_size),
2446 errors::InvalidArgument(
2447 strings::StrCat("Index ", index, " at offset ", i,
2448 " in indices is out of range")));
2449 auto a = accum_flat.template chip<0>(index);
2450 auto g = grad_flat.template chip<0>(i);
2451 auto v = var_flat.template chip<0>(index);
2452 a = a * a.constant(momentum_scalar) + g;
2453 if (use_nesterov_) {
2454 v -= g.constant(lr_scalar) * g +
2455 a.constant(lr_scalar) * a.constant(momentum_scalar) * a;
2456 } else {
2457 v -= a.constant(lr_scalar) * a;
2458 }
2459 }
2460 }
2461
2462 MaybeForwardRefInputToRefOutput(ctx, 0, 0);
2463 }
2464
2465 private:
2466 bool use_exclusive_lock_;
2467 bool use_nesterov_;
2468};

2475 SparseApplyMomentumOp<T, Tindices>); \

3106 mom_ = mom_ * mom_.constant(momentum_scalar) +

3400template <typename Device, typename T>
3401class ApplyPowerSignOp : public OpKernel {
3402 public:
3403 explicit ApplyPowerSignOp(OpKernelConstruction* ctx) : OpKernel(ctx) {
3404 OP_REQUIRES_OK(ctx, ctx->GetAttr("use_locking", &use_exclusive_lock_));
3405 }
3406
3407 void Compute(OpKernelContext* ctx) override {
3408 auto locks =
3409 MaybeLockVariableInputMutexesInOrder(ctx, use_exclusive_lock_, {0, 1});
3410
3411 Tensor var;
3412 OP_REQUIRES_OK(ctx, GetInputTensorFromVariable<Device, T>(
3413 ctx, 0, use_exclusive_lock_, false, &var));
3414 Tensor m;
3415 OP_REQUIRES_OK(ctx, GetInputTensorFromVariable<Device, T>(
3416 ctx, 1, use_exclusive_lock_, false, &m));
3417 OP_REQUIRES(
3418 ctx, var.IsInitialized(),
3419 errors::FailedPrecondition(
3420 "Attempting to use uninitialized variables: ", requested_input(0)));
3421 OP_REQUIRES(
3422 ctx, m.IsInitialized(),
3423 errors::FailedPrecondition(
3424 "Attempting to use uninitialized variables: ", requested_input(1)));
3425 const Tensor& lr = ctx->input(2);
3426 OP_REQUIRES(ctx, TensorShapeUtils::IsScalar(lr.shape()),
3427 errors::InvalidArgument("lr is not a scalar: ",
3428 lr.shape().DebugString()));
3429 const Tensor& logbase = ctx->input(3);
3430 OP_REQUIRES(ctx, TensorShapeUtils::IsScalar(logbase.shape()),
3431 errors::InvalidArgument("logbase is not a scalar: ",
3432 logbase.shape().DebugString()));
3433 const Tensor& sign_decay = ctx->input(4);
3434 OP_REQUIRES(ctx, TensorShapeUtils::IsScalar(logbase.shape()),
3435 errors::InvalidArgument("sign_decay is not a scalar: ",
3436 sign_decay.shape().DebugString()));
3437 const Tensor& beta = ctx->input(5);
3438 OP_REQUIRES(ctx, TensorShapeUtils::IsScalar(beta.shape()),
3439 errors::InvalidArgument("beta is not a scalar: ",
3440 beta.shape().DebugString()));
3441 const Tensor& grad = ctx->input(6);
3442 OP_REQUIRES(ctx, var.shape().IsSameSize(m.shape()),
3443 errors::InvalidArgument("var and m do not have the same shape",
3444 var.shape().DebugString(), " ",
3445 m.shape().DebugString()));
3446 OP_REQUIRES(
3447 ctx, var.shape().IsSameSize(grad.shape()),
3448 errors::InvalidArgument("var and grad do not have the same shape",
3449 var.shape().DebugString(), " ",
3450 grad.shape().DebugString()));
3451
3452 const Device& device = ctx->template eigen_device<Device>();
3453 functor::ApplyPowerSign<Device, T>()(
3454 device, var.flat<T>(), m.flat<T>(), lr.scalar<T>(), logbase.scalar<T>(),
3455 sign_decay.scalar<T>(), beta.scalar<T>(), grad.flat<T>());
3456 MaybeForwardRefInputToRefOutput(ctx, 0, 0);
3457 }
3458
3459 private:
3460 bool use_exclusive_lock_;
3461};
